@benbc Does your call to `Client.list_entries()` pass a `filter_` argument?  It is quite likely that the overall number of log entries for a project could be huge.  In addition, you might want to limit the number of results you fetch, e.g.:

```python
def list_recent_entries(client, num_entries=10):
    retry_list_entries = Retry()(client.list_entries)
    count = 0
    for entry in client.list_entries(order_by=DESCENDING):
        _do_something_with(entry)
        count += 1
        if count > num_entries:
            break
```

FWIW, a `409 Aborted` response is not one of the standard retryable exceptions (`DEADLINE_EXCEEDED`, `INTERNAL`, `UNAVAILABLE`).

Good spot.

While this is a very artificial case, I wonder if it's cleaner to just optimise away the double negation at the Snowball level, like so:

```
--- a/compiler/generator.c
+++ b/compiler/generator.c
@@ -313,6 +313,10 @@ static void generate_AE(struct generator * g, struct node * p) {
         case c_minint:
             write_string(g, "MININT"); break;
         case c_neg:
+            if (p->right->type == c_neg) {
+                generate_AE(g, p->right->right);
+                break;
+            }
             write_char(g, '-'); generate_AE(g, p->right); break;
         case c_multiply:
             s = " * "; goto label0;
```

Though it'd be better to do this in generic code than each backend.

