I'm still not sure I'm understanding your issue properly. From the code you've included I assume you want to apply some kind of validation to the input argument `str` in your mutation? If that is the case you can do that in the `mutate` method of the Mutation. That will allow you to return an accurate error message to the user.

E.g.:

```python
class TestMutate(graphene.Mutation):
	class Arguments:
		str = graphene.String(required=True)
	
	error_message = graphene.String()
	ok = graphene.Boolean(required=True)
	
	def mutate(root, info, str):
		# validate str
		try:
			validate_str(str)
			return TestMutate(ok=True)
		except StrTooLong:
			return TestMutate(error_message="Input string is too long", ok=False)
		except StrTooShort:
			return TestMutate(error_message="Input string is too short", ok=False)

```

