@back-to `platform.platform()` for macOS and Windows is not so friendly, I made a little function that has a nicer output:

```python
def os_version():
    # MAC OS X
    if sys.platform == "darwin":
        return "macOS {0}".format(platform.mac_ver()[0])
    # Windows
    elif sys.platform.startswith("win"):
        return "{0} {1}".format(platform.system(), platform.release())
    # linux / other
    else:
        return platform.platform()
```

